In [20]:
def inverse_exp_sigmoid(y, exponent=10.0, max_value=2.0, threshold=1e-7):
    sig_x_exp = (y-threshold)/max_value
    sig_x = sig_x_exp**1/tf.math.log(exponent)
    x = tf.math.log(sig_x/(1-sig_x))
    return x

The harmonic distribution of the DDSP inference (autoencoder):

(here I take the values after exp-sigmoid and inverse them)

It can be seen that lots of "vibration" or "noise" exist in harmonic distribution which is crucial to make things sound good. And the synthesizer parameters generator just smoothed it out.

And also I think those "vibration" or "noise" have some randomness in it, in a way similar to how f0 vibrato has different phase and fitting to a unimodal distribution will collapse the f0 to non-vibrato.
